  "description": "Coot-like waterbird with dark gray back and undersides with bright red frontal shield and white upper flank markings separating the lower brown back from lighter gray flanks. \u00a0Wings gray at base but chocolate brown otherwise as seen in flight and while swimming. White undertail coverts seen alos. Flies 2-3 times but only for a very short length, 10 meters or so. \u00a0Bobbed head when swimming which it did a lot (the swimming part). \u00a0Pecked on the water surface where a mat of algae and pond weeds were common. No calls heard.",
